label chapter11:

    # [Scene: Low Row | Morning]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_1 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant delivery truck, gull cries clipped by the wind]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, steady cello undercurrent]
    "You move through the Low Row with a practiced economy — flyers folded on your palm, a list of volunteer shifts tucked in the pocket over your heart. The neighborhood smells of wet concrete, frying plantains,"
    "and the sweet rot of kelp that the tide leaves behind. People glance up from doorways; some offer quiet nods, others study you like you're the last map they have."
    show maya_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "We'll be at the community center at two. Can you bring the hydrographs?"
    show rafi_odeh at right:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "I brought two sets and Lio's drone footage. You're not letting them steamroll this."
    "You watch Rafi adjust his gloves, the dirt in the cracked knuckles familiar and steady. You feel the old compass weight beneath your jacket though it no longer points. It anchors you anyway."
    "You promised a referendum because the calendar had been compressed into a chokehold. You promised because silence would make the seawall decision an administrative footnote. You promised to let people choose — and now you carry the consequences of that choice with every step."
    hide maya_corvin
    hide rafi_odeh

    scene bg ch9_3be532_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Your phone buzzes, feeds refreshing; the poster's glossy surface reflects the sun where a child runs by]
    "You pull up social feeds. The corporate ads have multiplied overnight — short, glossy spots of steel and smiling families, then cutaways to footage of flooded streets, trembling with scare-music just under the voiceover. They run"
    "the same phrase in different cadences: act now, protect livelihoods, avoid catastrophe. Even the municipal feed repeats the phrase, framed as 'urgent fiscal review.'"

    menu:
        "Film a neighborhood rebuttal":
            "You grab your tablet and record a two-minute rebuttal in the sun by the rooftop nursery, your voice shaking only at the edges as neighbors step into frame."
        "Organize a guided low-tide tour":
            "You call Rafi and Lio to lead a guided tour for reporters, hoping the tangible damage will outshine slick renders."
        "Focus on paperwork and permits":
            "You tuck your phone away and pore over the signatures — every name is a line of responsibility; you imagine their faces when the ballots arrive."

    # --- merge ---
    "The day continues regardless of the tactical choice; you carry the outcomes forward into the next meetings."
    # [Scene: Municipal Hall | Late Morning]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Quiet murmurs, the hum of climate control]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Subtle strings that tighten into a minor chord]

    "You enter municipal hall with the petition folder pressed to your chest. The atrium is busier than it should be — reporters, investors, municipal staff with watchful eyes. The idea of "public choosing" has rattled more than a few cages. At the reception desk, a screen shows the day's headlines" "Markets Watch Nueva Mar,' 'Investors Seek Clarity,' 'Mayor Velez's Calendar Tightens."
    show mayor_ana_velez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_ana_velez "Maya. We knew this would get loud. I hope you understand how delicate the city's balance is right now."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Delicate shouldn't mean surrendered."

    mayor_ana_velez "Delicate means people look at their savings and imagine one storm and everything gone. My calendar has been filled with closed-door calls. There are questions about bonds, about insurance — people are scared of the economic fallout, not just the weather."
    "You feel the thread in your hands fray. The municipal coffers are being bared like a wound; analysts in tidy suits point at spreadsheets and call it risk. Fear has a currency that buys attention, and attention bends policy."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant raised voice, the scrape of a chair]
    hide mayor_ana_velez
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_4 at full_bg
    "You listen while the bureaucrats parse the city's bottom line. It is exhausting and small and real. The room smells faintly of coffee gone cold and disinfectant. You think of the rooftop beds, of little hands planting seeds that will not be theirs if the wetlands are paved over."
    # [Scene: Neighborhood Canvass & Online Campaign | Afternoon → Evening]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_5 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Footsteps, murmur of conversation, a distant siren]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Medium-paced rhythm; a repeated motif that tightens as night comes]
    "You and your team push every lever you have. Lio tags murals with QR codes linking to testimonies; Rafi runs community meetings under tarps. You hold emergency training for flood response and livestream interviews with Dr."
    "Sima until your voice rasps. Each hour the corporate machine replies with a sharper tone — more dire footage, more rapid appeals to authority, to the 'experts' who say hard edges will save lives."
    show lio_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lio_corvin "They've started a fake testimonial campaign. Someone cloned Mrs. Ortega's voice."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "We'll fact-check it and post the real one. We can out-truth them, Lio. People will listen."

    lio_corvin "Do you think they will?"
    "You do not know. The mid-level panic hums in your chest; it is not hysteria, but a pressure that demands proof. Your strategy is simple — make the stakes visible in human terms — but the opposition weaponizes fear into immediacy: vote this and be safe now."

    menu:
        "Spend the night canvassing with Lio":
            "You pull your jacket tight and knock doors with Lio into the cool hours, listening to people list what they'd lose — their small businesses, their children's futures — and pinning those losses to the petition."
        "Run a final evidence livestream":
            "You gather Dr. Sima and a handful of neighbors for a livestream, the models and faces layered together as you try to pierce the sea of ads with reality."

    # --- merge ---
    "Dawn arrives and voting day proceeds; the immediate tactical effects fold into the broader turnout."
    # [Scene: Polling Stations | Voting Day — Dawn to Dusk]
    hide lio_corvin
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_6 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Murmurs, the clack of ballots; a child laughing in the distance]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A steady tempo that becomes an anxious undercurrent]
    "Voting day arrives with a low overcast sky. Turnout is high — more people than you expected, drawn by fear, by solidarity, by curiosity. Poll workers move with kind, wearied efficiency. You stand in line, the paper ballot warm and familiar in your hand."
    "You feel the gravity of the moment in the small weight of that ballot. This is what democracy looks like when it is raw and unshielded: citizens making choices beneath a sky that could change at any hour."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The rustle of paper, a volunteer's shouted encouragement]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_7 at full_bg
    "You run into Elias between stations, a flash of slate blue in the crowd. His face is drawn, rims shadowed. For a second you let yourself imagine that there will be a breath of relief when the count starts, that reason and local knowledge will tip the scale."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "Maya."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "You came. Thank you."

    elias_kahn "Of course. I—' [he pauses, choosing] 'I wanted to be here for you."
    "His hand is briefly on your shoulder, then gone. He is holding something back — not a refusal, but a retreat into procedure, into the safety of institutions."

    elias_kahn "They called an emergency session at City Hall. The Mayor wants a full audit of the amendment's fiscal impacts. They asked me to serve on the committee."

    maya_corvin "You'll be on the inside."

    elias_kahn "I'll be busy, Maya. They'll keep me tied to briefings and numbers. I can help where I can...but it will be slow, and it will be far from the Low Row."

    maya_corvin "Is that— is that your way of stepping back?"

    elias_kahn "No. I— I can't do everything. This is not just about will; it's about the leverage I can have. If I take this role, I can stall some of the worst impulses. But I won't be at every wake, at every rally. I'm sorry."
    "His apology hangs between you like a small, inadequate flag. You see the logic — municipal process as armor — and the absence: the warmth and proximity that used to make conversation feel like repair. The distance between public duty and private presence yawns."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant bell; the counting begins; murmurs swell]
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_8 at full_bg
    # [Scene: Municipal Hall — Results Projection | Evening]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_9 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A collective inhalation, a cough; the queue of updates pings on phones]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single chord held and then released into a minor progression]
    "The results come in slow and precise. The numbers arrive like little knocks. The projection confirms what the ads had prepared the ground for: a narrow approval for the corporate seawall. The screen shows percentages that could have been reversed by a few dozen votes. You feel the floor tilt."
    "The approval is not a roar of triumph; it's a thin, brittle sound. People cheer in some pockets, cry in others. The decision is made in public, by public fear and the promise of security. You"
    "realize the referendum did what you asked — it forced a debate — and yet the debate answered with urgency over care."

    scene bg ch9_3be532_10 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Clang of metal, diesel engines, the first pour of concrete sloshing into forms]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low mechanical rhythm; a dirge-like undertone]
    "You go to the shoreline the morning crews mobilize. The seawall work begins with a clinical efficiency. Chains rattle. Concrete mixers cough. They cordon off the marsh with orange fencing and heavy stakes; you watch as"
    "sacred plots — a small shrine under a fig, a string of shells nailed to a board — are fenced and then leveled."
    "Wetlands you once measured by the reach of your boots are turned into construction zones. The lost spaces are both literal and mnemonic — the place where you taught neighborhood kids to plant marsh grass becomes a staging area for molds and rebar."

    scene bg ch9_3be532_11 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Footsteps stop; a momentary hush as two people cross paths]

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "This is the only way to get the city safe in time."
    show maya_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Safe for whom, Camila? You cut out corridors — the parts that make this place liveable."

    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro" "You asked for a vote. The vote decided. My job is to deliver what's been approved."
    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro's voice is a blade wrapped in leather. She commands the site like an orchestra conductor, each motion exact. Yet when you meet her gaze the second time, there's a flicker — something brief"
    "and human — the glint of a small porcelain pendant at her throat as she turns away. It is a private thing, too delicate for the hard lines of her uniform."

    menu:
        "Call out the workers, record a protest":
            "You lift your voice and film as neighbors chant, the sound echoing against metal — for a moment the chant disrupts the cadence of construction, then is absorbed into the machinery's noise."
        "Walk the perimeter and catalogue losses":
            "You trace the new boundary with your hand on the orange mesh, counting the trees fenced out and the graves of small nurseries you will have to remember for everyone else."

    # --- merge ---
    "The site continues; the immediate protest or documentation informs the community's records and memories."
    # [Scene: Low Row — Aftermath | Dusk]
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_12 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A lullaby sung softly in a doorway, the distant thump of a generator]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Sparse piano, each note a small, aching interval]
    "The Low Row changes shape in front of you. A neighbor you grew up with packs a battered truck at dusk — she leaves in the thick, resigned silence of someone who has run out of"
    "options. Another family holds a vigil at the corner where their garden used to be; candles bob in jars, their light trembling like small boats."
    show lio_corvin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lio_corvin "They took the wall right across the mural. I tried to save the image."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "We can document it. We can press for recollection, at least."

    lio_corvin "Documentation doesn't fill a garden."
    show rafi_odeh at center:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "You made them look, Maya. That matters."
    "Rafi says the thing that both comforts and cuts. You did make them look. You made the ballot reflect a choice. But the choice favored immediate security over the living, breathing system you tried to protect. The wound is not only physical; it is moral."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Distant clink of tools, the metallic song of construction continuing through the night]
    hide lio_corvin
    hide maya_corvin
    hide rafi_odeh

    scene bg ch9_3be532_13 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: The piano drops out; a single cello note lingers]
    "You stand at the water's new edge while concrete still smells of riverbed and oil. The sea has been reshaped by human hands into something the city can measure, price, and insure. You measure loss not"
    "only in square meters but in the small places: a child's handprint in wet clay, a shrine's loosened nail, a song no longer sung at dawn."
    "The referendum did what it was meant to do: it made the question communal. The answer came in a voice you could not command — the voice of wide, ragged fear. You watch the crews lay"
    "concrete where marsh grass had been, and the weight of it presses into you like a tide."
    # [Scene: A Narrow Alley Beside the Boarded Nursery | Night]

    scene bg ch9_3be532_14 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A soft exhale; far-off machinery continues]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Minimal strings, a thin, mournful line]
    "Elias appears there by chance or by design. He stands at the mouth of the alley, hands in pockets, the light catching the silver streak at his temple. He has the committee badge clipped to his coat like an armor piece."
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "I took the committee. It seemed like the most useful thing I could do."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Useful for them."

    elias_kahn "For the people, too. Policies don't change because of chants alone. I can buy time in meetings. I can keep them from bulldozing more than necessary."

    maya_corvin "Is that the same as being here? Is it the same as standing with a neighbor as they pack their life into boxes?"

    elias_kahn "No. It's not. I'm sorry for that."
    "There's a world of negotiation inside his apology. You want to blame him and you want to thank him — both at once. The conflict between method and presence snaps taut."

    elias_kahn "I didn't leave you. I thought I could keep the system from doing worse from the inside."

    maya_corvin "Inside can be very far."

    elias_kahn "I know."
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_15 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The rattle of a passing truck; a child's laugh faint and distant]
    show elias_kahn at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elias_kahn "I wish I could have done it another way."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "So do I."
    "He moves away into the night and the committees that will occupy his days. The comfort you thought you might find in his proximity dissolves into the bureaucratic distance of his new role. The wound is both personal and civic."
    # [Scene: Low Row — Night Vigil | Late Night]
    hide elias_kahn
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_16 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Quiet murmurs, someone singing an old sea shanty]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, aching chord held steady]
    "Neighbors stand watch. They hold candles for the plots taken, for the elders forced to move, for the children who will not know the old marsh. You hold a photograph of the Promenade — when it was whole — its edges curled with salt."
    show rafi_odeh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    rafi_odeh "We will keep telling the story. We will map the lost places. We will be the memory."
    show maya_corvin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_corvin "Will remembering be enough?"

    rafi_odeh "It has to be. For now, it is all we have."
    "You let the sentence sit. In the morning the construction will continue. The wall will be poured and set. People will make new routines or leave. Your referendum forced the city to choose; the city chose"
    "fear's promise over the uncertain work of care. You are left with a sense of loss that has the clarity of a shard."
    hide rafi_odeh
    hide maya_corvin

    scene bg ch9_3be532_17 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single, small piano motif — not resolution, only a memory of there once being a chord]
    "You stand at the fence and watch a young worker pour a smooth gray seam into the ocean's edge. It hardens as your breath fogs in the night air. Somewhere across the site, beneath the floodlights,"
    "Camila 'Kai' Navarro pauses with her hand resting on the edge of a mural, a porcelain pendant catching the light like a tiny, unavailing star. Elias will be in committee tomorrow. Lio will paint the loss"
    "into a thousand murals. Rafi will organize vigils. You have forced the debate and watched it answer with scarcity and fear. The question now is not whether you blinked — it is what you will do"
    "next."

    scene bg ch9_3be532_18 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fade Out]

    jump chapter14
